Implemented in `app/auth.py` and `app/main.py`.

What changed
- `app/auth.py`
  - `require_api_key` now reads `X-API-Key`, validates against `VALID_API_KEYS`, returns the username, and raises `HTTPException(401)` for missing or invalid keys.

- `app/main.py`
  - `GET /tasks` now supports optional combinable filters:
    - `status`
    - `priority`
    - `assigned_to`
  - `GET /tasks` now supports pagination:
    - `page` default `1`, minimum `1`
    - `page_size` default `20`, minimum `1`
  - Added `POST /tasks`
    - requires auth
    - validates `project_id`
    - returns `404` if project missing
    - auto-generates integer task IDs
    - returns created task with `201`
  - Added `PUT /tasks/{task_id}`
    - requires auth
    - partial updates for `title`, `status`, `priority`, `assigned_to`
    - returns `404` if task missing
  - Added `DELETE /tasks/{task_id}`
    - requires auth
    - returns `404` if task missing
    - returns `204` on success
  - Added small helpers to keep handlers simple:
    - `find_task`
    - `project_exists`
    - `get_next_task_id`
    - `replace_task`

Validation
- `python -m compileall app run.py` passed.
- LSP diagnostics for `app/auth.py` and `app/main.py` reported no issues.
- `pytest -x --tb=short` found no tests in this repo, so there was nothing to run.

One adjacent issue: there are currently no API tests, so these behaviors are only syntax-checked, not behavior-verified.
